#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn26:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 26 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 26 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn26:0.2"
msgid "Cakkavattisutta "
msgstr "The Wheel-Turning Monarch "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:0.3"
msgid "1. Attadīpasaraṇatā "
msgstr "1. Taking Refuge in Oneself "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli3.58, sc1
msgctxt "dn26:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn26:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā magadhesu viharati mātulāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Magadhans at Mātulā. "

msgctxt "dn26:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "dn26:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:1.5"
msgid "“Bhaddante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn26:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "dn26:1.7"
msgid "“Attadīpā, bhikkhave, viharatha attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, be your own island, your own refuge, with no other refuge. Let the teaching be your island and your refuge, with no other refuge. "

msgctxt "dn26:1.8"
msgid "Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant do this? "

msgctxt "dn26:1.9"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "dn26:1.10"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "dn26:1.11"
msgid "citte cittānupassī … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "dn26:1.12"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "dn26:1.13"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is their own island, their own refuge, with no other refuge. That’s how they let the teaching be their island and their refuge, with no other refuge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "dn26:1.14"
msgid "Gocare, bhikkhave, caratha sake pettike visaye. "
msgstr "You should roam inside your own territory, the domain of your fathers. "

#. VAR: ārammaṇaṃ → āramaṇaṃ (?)
msgctxt "dn26:1.15"
msgid "Gocare, bhikkhave, carataṃ sake pettike visaye na lacchati māro otāraṃ, na lacchati māro ārammaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "If you roam inside your own territory, the domain of your fathers, Māra won’t catch you or get hold of you. "

# NOTE: This line feels awkward, and I suspect that both here and in its recurrence at the end it is clumsily inserted. It’s not clear what “idam” refers to. Both RD and MW translate “evamidam” as if it were eva’m’idam, but this is unlikely. Evamidam is used to indicate entailment, eg MN 73. Comm: “Evamidaṃ puññaṃ pavaḍḍhatīti evaṃ idaṃ lokiyalokuttaraṃ puññaphalaṃ vaḍḍhati, puññaphalanti ca uparūpari puññampi puññavipākopi veditabbo.”
msgctxt "dn26:1.16"
msgid "Kusalānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ samādānahetu evamidaṃ puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "It is due to undertaking skillful qualities that this merit grows. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:1.17"
msgid "2. Daḷhanemicakkavattirājā "
msgstr "2. King Daḷhanemi "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli3.59, sc4
#. VAR: cakkavattī → cakkavatti (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:2.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā daḷhanemi nāma ahosi cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, mendicants, there was a king named Daḷhanemi who was a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion extended to all four sides, he achieved stability in the country, and he possessed the seven treasures. "

msgctxt "dn26:2.2"
msgid "Tassimāni satta ratanāni ahesuṃ seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "He had the following seven treasures: "

msgctxt "dn26:2.3"
msgid "cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr "the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure. "

msgctxt "dn26:2.4"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā ahesuṃ sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr "He had over a thousand sons who were valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of his enemies. "

#. VAR: asatthena dhammena → dhammena samena (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn26:2.5"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasi. "
msgstr "After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigned by principle, without rod or sword. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, pts-vp-pli3.60, sc5
msgctxt "dn26:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā daḷhanemi bahunnaṃ vassānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, King Daḷhanemi addressed one of his men, "

# NOTE: osakkati: like a woman shrinking away from a man’s advances (DN 12), or a ram drawing back getting ready to charge (Ja 324).
msgctxt "dn26:3.2"
msgid "‘yadā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, passeyyāsi dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutaṃ, atha me āroceyyāsī’ti. "
msgstr "‘My good man, when you see that the heavenly wheel-treasure has receded back from its place, please tell me.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:3.3"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, so puriso rañño daḷhanemissa paccassosi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied that man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:3.4"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, so puriso bahunnaṃ vassānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutaṃ, disvāna yena rājā daḷhanemi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ daḷhanemiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "After many thousand years had passed, that man saw that the heavenly wheel-treasure had receded back from its place. So he went to King Daḷhanemi and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:3.5"
msgid "‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, dibbaṃ te cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Please sire, you should know that your heavenly wheel-treasure has receded back from its place.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: āmantāpetvā → āmantetvā (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn26:3.6"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā daḷhanemi jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "So the king summoned the crown prince and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:3.7"
msgid "‘dibbaṃ kira me, tāta kumāra, cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Dear prince, my heavenly wheel-treasure has receded back from its place. "

msgctxt "dn26:3.8"
msgid "Sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ—"
msgstr "I’ve heard that "

msgctxt "dn26:3.9"
msgid "yassa rañño cakkavattissa dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkati ṭhānā cavati, na dāni tena raññā ciraṃ jīvitabbaṃ hotīti. "
msgstr "when this happens to a wheel-turning monarch, he does not have long to live. "

msgctxt "dn26:3.10"
msgid "Bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā, samayo dāni me dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ. "
msgstr "I have enjoyed human pleasures. Now it is time for me to seek heavenly pleasures. "

msgctxt "dn26:3.11"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ paṭipajja. "
msgstr "Come, dear prince, rule this land surrounded by ocean! "

msgctxt "dn26:3.12"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I shall shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "dn26:3.13"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā daḷhanemi jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji. "
msgstr "And so, after carefully instructing the crown prince in kingship, King Daḷhanemi shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "dn26:3.14"
msgid "Sattāhapabbajite kho pana, bhikkhave, rājisimhi dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ antaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Seven days later the heavenly wheel-treasure vanished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc7
#. VAR: muddhābhisitto → muddhāvasitto (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro puriso yena rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ khattiyaṃ muddhābhisittaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a certain man approached the newly anointed aristocrat king and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:4.2"
msgid "‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ antarahitan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Please sire, you should know that the heavenly wheel-treasure has vanished.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto dibbe cakkaratane antarahite anattamano ahosi, anattamanatañca paṭisaṃvedesi. "
msgstr "At that the king was unhappy and experienced unhappiness. "

msgctxt "dn26:4.4"
msgid "So yena rājisi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājisiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He went to the royal sage and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:4.5"
msgid "‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ antarahitan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Please sire, you should know that the heavenly wheel-treasure has vanished.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, rājisi rājānaṃ khattiyaṃ muddhābhisittaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, the royal sage said to him, "

msgctxt "dn26:4.7"
msgid "‘mā kho tvaṃ, tāta, dibbe cakkaratane antarahite anattamano ahosi, mā anattamanatañca paṭisaṃvedesi, na hi te, tāta, dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ pettikaṃ dāyajjaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Don’t be unhappy at the vanishing of the wheel-treasure. My dear, the wheel-treasure is not inherited from your father. "

# NOTE: Since this is the only place where ariya qualifies cakkavatti, I assume it refers to the duties, similar to ariyavinaya. Also see the title below, Cakkavattiariyavatta
msgctxt "dn26:4.8"
msgid "Iṅgha tvaṃ, tāta, ariye cakkavattivatte vattāhi. "
msgstr "Come now, my dear, implement the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

#. VAR: sīsaṃnhātassa → sīsaṃ nahātassa (bj, pts1) | sīsanhātassa (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:4.9"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ te ariye cakkavattivatte vattamānassa tadahuposathe pannarase sīsaṃnhātassa uposathikassa uparipāsādavaragatassa dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ pātubhavissati sahassāraṃ sanemikaṃ sanābhikaṃ sabbākāraparipūran’ti. "
msgstr "If you do so, it’s possible that—on a fifteenth day sabbath, having bathed your head and gone upstairs in the stilt longhouse to observe the sabbath—the heavenly wheel-treasure will appear to you, with a thousand spokes, with rim and hub, complete in every detail.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn26:4.10"
msgid "2.1. Cakkavattiariyavatta "
msgstr "2.1. The Noble Duties of a Wheel-Turning Monarch "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, pts-vp-pli3.61, sc8
msgctxt "dn26:5.1"
msgid "‘Katamaṃ pana taṃ, deva, ariyaṃ cakkavattivattan’ti? "
msgstr "‘But sire, what are the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: saṃvidahassu is second middle imperative
#. VAR: anuyantesu → anuyuttesu (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: garuṃ karonto → garukaronto (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:5.2"
msgid "‘Tena hi tvaṃ, tāta, dhammaṃyeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ mānento dhammaṃ pūjento dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahassu antojanasmiṃ balakāyasmiṃ khattiyesu anuyantesu brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamajānapadesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu migapakkhīsu. "
msgstr "‘Well then, my dear, relying only on principle—honoring, respecting, and venerating principle, having principle as your flag, banner, and authority—provide just protection and security for your court, troops, aristocrats, vassals, brahmins and householders, people of town and country, ascetics and brahmins, beasts and birds. "

# NOTE: pavattittha is aorist middle. Curiously, (a)dhammakāra doesn’t seem to occur elswehere in the EBTs. It does occur in Ja 513 and Ja 498, both times in the context of just rule: Adhammakāro tava māhu raṭṭhe
msgctxt "dn26:5.3"
msgid "Mā ca te, tāta, vijite adhammakāro pavattittha. "
msgstr "Do not let injustice prevail in the realm. "

# NOTE: While anuppadeti is given in the dicts in the sense of “give, hand over”, in the nikayas it seems to be restricted to “pay” in the sense of a just reward for work, or return on a loan. While I wouldn’t want to over-interpret it, it is an interesting choice here, which suggests more “pay them a fair wage “than” support them with charity”.
msgctxt "dn26:5.4"
msgid "Ye ca te, tāta, vijite adhanā assu, tesañca dhanamanuppadeyyāsi. "
msgstr "Pay money to the penniless in the realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Where this idiom occurs elsewhere, it is inevitably with paripucchati paripañhati. PTS here omits the second verb. Comm is silent. Generally the suttas are very precise about the sequence of learning: first you ask, then you listen, then you learn. Most likely this is a mistake here.
msgctxt "dn26:5.5"
msgid "Ye ca te, tāta, vijite samaṇabrāhmaṇā madappamādā paṭiviratā khantisoracce niviṭṭhā ekamattānaṃ damenti, ekamattānaṃ samenti, ekamattānaṃ parinibbāpenti, te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā paripuccheyyāsi pariggaṇheyyāsi: "
msgstr "And there are ascetics and brahmins in the realm who avoid intoxication and negligence, are settled in patience and gentleness, and who tame, calm, and extinguish themselves. From time to time you should go up to them and ask: "

msgctxt "dn26:5.6"
msgid "“kiṃ, bhante, kusalaṃ, kiṃ akusalaṃ, kiṃ sāvajjaṃ, kiṃ anavajjaṃ, kiṃ sevitabbaṃ, kiṃ na sevitabbaṃ, kiṃ me karīyamānaṃ dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya assa, kiṃ vā pana me karīyamānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya assā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sirs, what is skillful? What is unskillful? What is blameworthy? What is blameless? What should be cultivated? What should not be cultivated? Doing what leads to my lasting harm and suffering? Doing what leads to my lasting welfare and happiness?” "

msgctxt "dn26:5.7"
msgid "Tesaṃ sutvā yaṃ akusalaṃ taṃ abhinivajjeyyāsi, yaṃ kusalaṃ taṃ samādāya vatteyyāsi. "
msgstr "Having heard them, you should reject what is unskillful and undertake and follow what is skillful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:5.8"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, tāta, taṃ ariyaṃ cakkavattivattan’ti. "
msgstr "These are the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn26:5.9"
msgid "2.2. Cakkaratanapātubhāva "
msgstr "2.2. The Wheel-Treasure Appears "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.62, sc9
msgctxt "dn26:5.10"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto rājisissa paṭissutvā ariye cakkavattivatte vatti. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the new king to the royal sage. And he implemented the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:5.11"
msgid "Tassa ariye cakkavattivatte vattamānassa tadahuposathe pannarase sīsaṃnhātassa uposathikassa uparipāsādavaragatassa "
msgstr "While he was implementing them, on a fifteenth day sabbath, he had bathed his head and gone upstairs in the stilt longhouse to observe the sabbath. "

msgctxt "dn26:5.12"
msgid "dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ pāturahosi sahassāraṃ sanemikaṃ sanābhikaṃ sabbākāraparipūraṃ. "
msgstr "And the heavenly wheel-treasure appeared to him, with a thousand spokes, with rim and hub, complete in every detail. "

msgctxt "dn26:5.13"
msgid "Disvāna rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Seeing this, the king thought, "

msgctxt "dn26:5.14"
msgid "‘sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ—yassa rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa tadahuposathe pannarase sīsaṃnhātassa uposathikassa uparipāsādavaragatassa dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ pātubhavati sahassāraṃ sanemikaṃ sanābhikaṃ sabbākāraparipūraṃ, so hoti rājā cakkavattīti. "
msgstr "‘I have heard that when the heavenly wheel-treasure appears to a king in this way, he becomes a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:5.15"
msgid "Assaṃ nu kho ahaṃ rājā cakkavattī’ti. "
msgstr "Am I then a wheel-turning monarch?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, sc10
msgctxt "dn26:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vāmena hatthena bhiṅkāraṃ gahetvā dakkhiṇena hatthena cakkaratanaṃ abbhukkiri: "
msgstr "Then the anointed king, rising from his seat and arranging his robe over one shoulder, took a ceremonial vase in his left hand and besprinkled the wheel-treasure with his right hand, saying, "

msgctxt "dn26:6.2"
msgid "‘pavattatu bhavaṃ cakkaratanaṃ, abhivijinātu bhavaṃ cakkaratanan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Roll forth, O wheel-treasure! Triumph, O wheel-treasure!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "dn26:6.3"
msgid "Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, cakkaratanaṃ puratthimaṃ disaṃ pavatti, anvadeva rājā cakkavattī saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. Yasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, padese cakkaratanaṃ patiṭṭhāsi, tattha rājā cakkavattī vāsaṃ upagacchi saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. "
msgstr "Then the wheel-treasure rolled towards the east. And the king followed it together with his army of four divisions. In whatever place the wheel-treasure stood still, there the king came to stay together with his army. "

msgctxt "dn26:6.4"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, puratthimāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "And any opposing rulers of the eastern quarter came to the wheel-turning monarch and said, "

#. VAR: svāgataṃ te → svāgataṃ (s1-3) | sāgataṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:6.5"
msgid "‘ehi kho, mahārāja, svāgataṃ te mahārāja, sakaṃ te, mahārāja, anusāsa, mahārājā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come, great king! Welcome, great king! We are yours, great king, instruct us.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:6.6"
msgid "Rājā cakkavattī evamāha: "
msgstr "The wheel-turning monarch said, "

msgctxt "dn26:6.7"
msgid "‘pāṇo na hantabbo, adinnaṃ nādātabbaṃ, kāmesumicchā na caritabbā, musā na bhāsitabbā, majjaṃ na pātabbaṃ, yathābhuttañca bhuñjathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Do not kill living creatures. Do not steal. Do not commit sexual misconduct. Do not lie. Do not drink alcohol. Maintain the current level of taxation.’ "

#. VAR: anuyantā → anuyuttā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:6.8"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, puratthimāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rañño cakkavattissa anuyantā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so the opposing rulers of the eastern quarter became his vassals. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, pts-vp-pli3.63, sc12
#. VAR: ajjhogāhetvā → ajjhogāhitvā (bj) | ajjhogahetvā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn26:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, cakkaratanaṃ puratthimaṃ samuddaṃ ajjhogāhetvā paccuttaritvā dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ pavatti … pe … "
msgstr "Then the wheel-treasure, having plunged into the eastern ocean and emerged again, rolled towards the south. … "

msgctxt "dn26:7.2"
msgid "dakkhiṇaṃ samuddaṃ ajjhogāhetvā paccuttaritvā pacchimaṃ disaṃ pavatti, anvadeva rājā cakkavattī saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. "
msgstr "Having plunged into the southern ocean and emerged again, it rolled towards the west. … "

#. VAR: padese cakkaratanaṃ → dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ (bj, c1)
msgctxt "dn26:7.3"
msgid "Yasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, padese cakkaratanaṃ patiṭṭhāsi, tattha rājā cakkavattī vāsaṃ upagacchi saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:7.4"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, pacchimāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:7.5"
msgid "‘ehi kho, mahārāja, svāgataṃ te, mahārāja, sakaṃ te, mahārāja, anusāsa, mahārājā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:7.6"
msgid "Rājā cakkavattī evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:7.7"
msgid "‘pāṇo na hantabbo, adinnaṃ nādātabbaṃ, kāmesumicchā na caritabbā, musā na bhāsitabbā, majjaṃ na pātabbaṃ, yathābhuttañca bhuñjathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:7.8"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, pacchimāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rañño cakkavattissa anuyantā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "dn26:7.9"
msgid "Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, cakkaratanaṃ pacchimaṃ samuddaṃ ajjhogāhetvā paccuttaritvā uttaraṃ disaṃ pavatti, anvadeva rājā cakkavattī saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. "
msgstr "Having plunged into the western ocean and emerged again, it rolled towards the north, followed by the king together with his army of four divisions. "

#. VAR: padese cakkaratanaṃ → dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ (bj, c1)
msgctxt "dn26:7.10"
msgid "Yasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, padese cakkaratanaṃ patiṭṭhāsi, tattha rājā cakkavattī vāsaṃ upagacchi saddhiṃ caturaṅginiyā senāya. "
msgstr "In whatever place the wheel-treasure stood still, there the king came to stay together with his army. "

msgctxt "dn26:7.11"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, uttarāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "And any opposing rulers of the northern quarter came to the wheel-turning monarch and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:7.12"
msgid "‘ehi kho, mahārāja, svāgataṃ te, mahārāja, sakaṃ te, mahārāja, anusāsa, mahārājā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come, great king! Welcome, great king! We are yours, great king, instruct us.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:7.13"
msgid "Rājā cakkavattī evamāha: "
msgstr "The wheel-turning monarch said, "

msgctxt "dn26:7.14"
msgid "‘pāṇo na hantabbo, adinnaṃ nādātabbaṃ, kāmesumicchā na caritabbā, musā na bhāsitabbā, majjaṃ na pātabbaṃ, yathābhuttañca bhuñjathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Do not kill living creatures. Do not steal. Do not commit sexual misconduct. Do not lie. Do not drink alcohol. Maintain the current level of taxation.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:7.15"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bhikkhave, uttarāya disāya paṭirājāno, te rañño cakkavattissa anuyantā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so the rulers of the northern quarter became his vassals. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/does-a-akara-a-mean-judgment-hall/3399
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "dn26:7.16"
msgid "Atha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, cakkaratanaṃ samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ abhivijinitvā tameva rājadhāniṃ paccāgantvā rañño cakkavattissa antepuradvāre atthakaraṇapamukhe akkhāhataṃ maññe aṭṭhāsi rañño cakkavattissa antepuraṃ upasobhayamānaṃ. "
msgstr "And then the wheel-treasure, having triumphed over this land surrounded by ocean, returned to the royal capital. There it stood still by the gate to the royal compound at the High Court as if fixed to an axle, illuminating the royal compound. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:7.17"
msgid "3. Dutiyādicakkavattikathā "
msgstr "3. On Subsequent Wheel-Turning Monarchs "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs8, pts-vp-pli3.64, sc15
msgctxt "dn26:8.1"
msgid "Dutiyopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī … pe … "
msgstr "And for a second time, "

msgctxt "dn26:8.2"
msgid "tatiyopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī … "
msgstr "and a third, "

msgctxt "dn26:8.3"
msgid "catutthopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī … "
msgstr "a fourth, "

msgctxt "dn26:8.4"
msgid "pañcamopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī … "
msgstr "a fifth, "

msgctxt "dn26:8.5"
msgid "chaṭṭhopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī … "
msgstr "a sixth, "

msgctxt "dn26:8.6"
msgid "sattamopi kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī bahunnaṃ vassānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "and a seventh time, a wheel-turning monarch was established in exactly the same way. And after many years the seventh wheel-turning monarch went forth, handing the realm over to the crown prince. "

msgctxt "dn26:8.7"
msgid "‘yadā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, passeyyāsi dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutaṃ, atha me āroceyyāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.8"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, so puriso rañño cakkavattissa paccassosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.9"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, so puriso bahunnaṃ vassānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahunnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.10"
msgid "Disvāna yena rājā cakkavattī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ cakkavattiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.11"
msgid "‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, dibbaṃ te cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ ṭhānā cutan’ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "dn26:8.12"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.13"
msgid "‘dibbaṃ kira me, tāta kumāra, cakkaratanaṃ osakkitaṃ, ṭhānā cutaṃ, sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.14"
msgid "yassa rañño cakkavattissa dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ osakkati, ṭhānā cavati, na dāni tena raññā ciraṃ jīvitabbaṃ hotīti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.15"
msgid "Bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā, samayo dāni me dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ, ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ paṭipajja. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.16"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "dn26:8.17"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:8.18"
msgid "Sattāhapabbajite kho pana, bhikkhave, rājisimhi dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ antaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Seven days later the heavenly wheel-treasure vanished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs9, sc18
msgctxt "dn26:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro puriso yena rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ khattiyaṃ muddhābhisittaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a certain man approached the newly anointed aristocrat king and said, "

msgctxt "dn26:9.2"
msgid "‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, dibbaṃ cakkaratanaṃ antarahitan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Please sire, you should know that the heavenly wheel-treasure has vanished.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:9.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto dibbe cakkaratane antarahite anattamano ahosi. Anattamanatañca paṭisaṃvedesi; "
msgstr "At that the king was unhappy and experienced unhappiness. "

msgctxt "dn26:9.4"
msgid "no ca kho rājisiṃ upasaṅkamitvā ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ pucchi. "
msgstr "But he didn’t go to the royal sage and ask about the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:9.5"
msgid "So samateneva sudaṃ janapadaṃ pasāsati. "
msgstr "He just governed the country according to his own ideas. "

# NOTE: I don’t know what pabbanti means, but comm sensibly has “na pabbantīti na vaḍḍhanti”. Note janapada in plural; extrapolating from the contemporary situation, it seems that the realm of the cakkavatti was comprised of several smaller nations. Both RD and MW mistranslate as “people” here.
msgctxt "dn26:9.6"
msgid "Tassa samatena janapadaṃ pasāsato pubbenāparaṃ janapadā na pabbanti, yathā taṃ pubbakānaṃ rājūnaṃ ariye cakkavattivatte vattamānānaṃ. "
msgstr "So governed, the nations did not prosper like before, as they had when former kings implemented the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

# NOTE: For anīkaṭṭhā, RD and MW both have “guards”. However comm says “Anīkaṭṭhāti hatthiācariyādayo”, which for some reason CPD thinks is worthy of an exclamation point. But surely this is reasonable: those in charge of the elephants and so on would have been important officials in the army. I think it is standing officers in the army, rather than royal guards as such. For mantassājīvino, RD and MW think it means chanters of mantras, but comm has “Mantassājīvinoti mantā vuccati paññā, taṃ nissayaṃ katvā ye jīvanti paṇḍitā mahāmattā, tesaṃ etaṃ nāmaṃ.”
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.65, sc19
msgctxt "dn26:9.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, amaccā pārisajjā gaṇakamahāmattā anīkaṭṭhā dovārikā mantassājīvino sannipatitvā rājānaṃ khattiyaṃ muddhābhisittaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the ministers and counselors, the treasury officials, military officers, guardsmen, and advisers gathered and said to the king, "

msgctxt "dn26:9.8"
msgid "‘na kho te, deva, samatena sudaṃ janapadaṃ pasāsato pubbenāparaṃ janapadā pabbanti, yathā taṃ pubbakānaṃ rājūnaṃ ariye cakkavattivatte vattamānānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Sire, when governed according to your own ideas, the nations do not prosper like before, as they did when former kings implemented the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:9.9"
msgid "Saṃvijjanti kho te, deva, vijite amaccā pārisajjā gaṇakamahāmattā anīkaṭṭhā dovārikā mantassājīvino mayañceva aññe ca ye mayaṃ ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ dhārema. "
msgstr "In your realm are found ministers and counselors, treasury officials, military officers, guardsmen, and advisers—both ourselves and others—who remember the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:9.10"
msgid "Iṅgha tvaṃ, deva, amhe ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ puccha. "
msgstr "Please, Your Majesty, ask us about the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:9.11"
msgid "Tassa te mayaṃ ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ puṭṭhā byākarissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "We will answer you.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:9.12"
msgid "4. Āyuvaṇṇādiparihānikathā "
msgstr "4. On the Period of Decline "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs10, pts-vp-pli3.66, sc20
#. VAR: ti → ādiyasīti (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto amacce pārisajje gaṇakamahāmatte anīkaṭṭhe dovārike mantassājīvino sannipātetvā ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ pucchi. "
msgstr "So the anointed king asked the assembled ministers and counselors, treasury officials, military officers, guardsmen, and advisers about the noble duties of a wheel-turning monarch. "

msgctxt "dn26:10.2"
msgid "Tassa te ariyaṃ cakkavattivattaṃ puṭṭhā byākariṃsu. "
msgstr "And they answered him. "

msgctxt "dn26:10.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ sutvā dhammikañhi kho rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahi, no ca kho adhanānaṃ dhanamanuppadāsi. "
msgstr "But after listening to them, he didn’t provide just protection and security. Nor did he pay money to the penniless in the realm. "

msgctxt "dn26:10.4"
msgid "Adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "And so poverty grew widespread. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.5"
msgid "Dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate aññataro puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "When poverty was widespread, a certain person stole from others, with the intention to commit theft. "

msgctxt "dn26:10.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aggahesuṃ. "
msgstr "They arrested him "

msgctxt "dn26:10.7"
msgid "Gahetvā rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa dassesuṃ: "
msgstr "and presented him to the king, saying, "

msgctxt "dn26:10.8"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this person stole from others with the intention to commit theft.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.9"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The king said to that person, "

msgctxt "dn26:10.10"
msgid "‘saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, ambho purisa, paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is it really true, mister, that you stole from others with the intention to commit theft?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.11"
msgid "‘Saccaṃ, devā’ti. "
msgstr "‘It’s true, sire.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.12"
msgid "‘Kiṃ kāraṇā’ti? "
msgstr "‘What was the reason?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.13"
msgid "‘Na hi, deva, jīvāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sire, I can’t survive.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.14"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto tassa purisassa dhanamanuppadāsi: "
msgstr "So the king paid some money to that person, saying, "

msgctxt "dn26:10.15"
msgid "‘iminā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, dhanena attanā ca jīvāhi, mātāpitaro ca posehi, puttadārañca posehi, kammante ca payojehi, samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpehi sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikan’ti. "
msgstr "‘With this money, mister, keep yourself alive, and provide for your mother and father, partners and children. Work for a living, and establish an uplifting religious donation for ascetics and brahmins that’s conducive to heaven, ripens in happiness, and leads to heaven.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:10.16"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, so puriso rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied that man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs11, sc21
msgctxt "dn26:11.1"
msgid "Aññataropi kho, bhikkhave, puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "But then another man stole something from others. "

msgctxt "dn26:11.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aggahesuṃ. "
msgstr "They arrested him "

msgctxt "dn26:11.3"
msgid "Gahetvā rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa dassesuṃ: "
msgstr "and presented him to the king, saying, "

msgctxt "dn26:11.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this person stole from others.’ "

