#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:12.14"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the king thought, "

msgctxt "dn26:12.15"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ yo yo paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyissati, tassa tassa dhanamanuppadassāmi, evamidaṃ adinnādānaṃ pavaḍḍhissati. "
msgstr "‘If I pay money to anyone who steals from others, it will only increase the stealing. "

#. VAR: mūlaghaccaṃ → mūlachejjaṃ (bj, mr) | mūlaghacchaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:12.16"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ purisaṃ sunisedhaṃ nisedheyyaṃ, mūlaghaccaṃ kareyyaṃ, sīsamassa chindeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "I’d better make an end of this person, finish him off, and chop off his head.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:12.17"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto purise āṇāpesi: "
msgstr "Then he ordered his men, "

#. VAR: pacchābāhaṃ → pacchābāhuṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:12.18"
msgid "‘tena hi, bhaṇe, imaṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhamitvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa sunisedhaṃ nisedhetha, mūlaghaccaṃ karotha, sīsamassa chindathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, my men, tie this man’s arms tightly behind his back with a strong rope. Shave his head and march him from street to street and square to square to the beating of a harsh drum. Then take him out the south gate and make an end of him, finish him off, and chop off his head.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:12.19"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, bhikkhave, te purisā rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa paṭissutvā taṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhamitvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa sunisedhaṃ nisedhesuṃ, mūlaghaccaṃ akaṃsu, sīsamassa chindiṃsu. "
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ they replied, and did as he commanded. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs13, pts-vp-pli3.68, sc23
msgctxt "dn26:13.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho, bhikkhave, manussā: "
msgstr "People heard about this: "

msgctxt "dn26:13.2"
msgid "‘ye kira, bho, paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyanti, te rājā sunisedhaṃ nisedheti, mūlaghaccaṃ karoti, sīsāni tesaṃ chindatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘It seems the king is chopping the head off anyone who steals from others!’ "

msgctxt "dn26:13.3"
msgid "Sutvāna tesaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to them, "

#. VAR: kārāpessāma → kārāpeyyāma (s1-3, pts1) | kārāpeyyāmāti (si)
msgctxt "dn26:13.4"
msgid "‘yannūna mayampi tiṇhāni satthāni kārāpessāma, tiṇhāni satthāni kārāpetvā yesaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyissāma, te sunisedhaṃ nisedhessāma, mūlaghaccaṃ karissāma, sīsāni tesaṃ chindissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘We’d better have sharp swords made. Then when we steal from others, we’ll make an end of them, finish them off, and chop off their heads.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:13.5"
msgid "Te tiṇhāni satthāni kārāpesuṃ, tiṇhāni satthāni kārāpetvā gāmaghātampi upakkamiṃsu kātuṃ, nigamaghātampi upakkamiṃsu kātuṃ, nagaraghātampi upakkamiṃsu kātuṃ, panthaduhanampi upakkamiṃsu kātuṃ. "
msgstr "They had sharp swords made. Then they started to make raids on villages, towns, and cities, and to infest the highways. "

msgctxt "dn26:13.6"
msgid "Yesaṃ te adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyanti, te sunisedhaṃ nisedhenti, mūlaghaccaṃ karonti, sīsāni tesaṃ chindanti. "
msgstr "And they chopped the heads off anyone they stole from. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs14, sc24
msgctxt "dn26:14.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi, dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate adinnādānaṃ vepullamagamāsi, adinnādāne vepullaṃ gate satthaṃ vepullamagamāsi, satthe vepullaṃ gate pāṇātipāto vepullamagamāsi, pāṇātipāte vepullaṃ gate tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, from not paying money to the penniless, poverty became widespread. When poverty was widespread, theft became widespread. When theft was widespread, swords became widespread. When swords were widespread, killing living creatures became widespread. And for the sentient beings among whom killing was widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:14.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ asītivassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ cattārīsavassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people lived for 80,000 years, but their children lived for 40,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "dn26:14.3"
msgid "Cattārīsavassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu aññataro puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 40,000 years, a certain person stole something from others. "

msgctxt "dn26:14.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aggahesuṃ. "
msgstr "They arrested him "

msgctxt "dn26:14.5"
msgid "Gahetvā rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa dassesuṃ: "
msgstr "and presented him to the king, saying, "

msgctxt "dn26:14.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this person stole from others.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:14.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The king said to that person, "

msgctxt "dn26:14.8"
msgid "‘saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, ambho purisa, paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is it really true, mister, that you stole from others?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn26:14.9"
msgid "‘Na hi, devā’ti sampajānamusā abhāsi. "
msgstr "‘No, sire,’ he said, deliberately lying. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs15, pts-vp-pli3.69, sc26
msgctxt "dn26:15.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi. Dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate adinnādānaṃ vepullamagamāsi, adinnādāne vepullaṃ gate satthaṃ vepullamagamāsi. Satthe vepullaṃ gate pāṇātipāto vepullamagamāsi, pāṇātipāte vepullaṃ gate musāvādo vepullamagamāsi, musāvāde vepullaṃ gate tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, from not paying money to the penniless, poverty, theft, swords, and killing became widespread. When killing was widespread, lying became widespread. And for the sentient beings among whom lying was widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:15.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ cattārīsavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vīsativassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 40,000 years had children who lived for 20,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "dn26:15.3"
msgid "Vīsativassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu aññataro puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 20,000 years, a certain person stole something from others. "

msgctxt "dn26:15.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro puriso rañño khattiyassa muddhābhisittassa ārocesi: "
msgstr "Someone else reported this to the king, "

msgctxt "dn26:15.5"
msgid "‘itthannāmo, deva, puriso paresaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyī’ti pesuññamakāsi. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, such-and-such person stole from others,’ he said, going behind his back. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs16, sc28
msgctxt "dn26:16.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi. Dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate adinnādānaṃ vepullamagamāsi, adinnādāne vepullaṃ gate satthaṃ vepullamagamāsi, satthe vepullaṃ gate pāṇātipāto vepullamagamāsi, pāṇātipāte vepullaṃ gate musāvādo vepullamagamāsi, musāvāde vepullaṃ gate pisuṇā vācā vepullamagamāsi, pisuṇāya vācāya vepullaṃ gatāya tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, from not paying money to the penniless, poverty, theft, swords, killing, and lying became widespread. When lying was widespread, backbiting became widespread. And for the sentient beings among whom backbiting was widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:16.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ vīsativassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ dasavassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 20,000 years had children who lived for 10,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs17, sc29
msgctxt "dn26:17.1"
msgid "Dasavassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ekidaṃ sattā vaṇṇavanto honti, ekidaṃ sattā dubbaṇṇā. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 10,000 years, some were more beautiful than others. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.2"
msgid "Tattha ye te sattā dubbaṇṇā, te vaṇṇavante satte abhijjhāyantā paresaṃ dāresu cārittaṃ āpajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "And the ugly beings, coveting the beautiful ones, committed adultery with others’ wives. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "dn26:17.3"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi. Dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate … pe … kāmesumicchācāro vepullamagamāsi, kāmesumicchācāre vepullaṃ gate tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, from not paying money to the penniless, poverty, theft, swords, killing, lying, and backbiting became widespread. When backbiting was widespread, sexual misconduct became widespread. And for the sentient beings among whom sexual misconduct was widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ dasavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ pañcavassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 10,000 years had children who lived for 5,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.70, sc31
msgctxt "dn26:17.5"
msgid "Pañcavassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu dve dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu—"
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 5,000 years, two things became widespread: "

msgctxt "dn26:17.6"
msgid "pharusāvācā samphappalāpo ca. "
msgstr "harsh speech and talking nonsense. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.7"
msgid "Dvīsu dhammesu vepullaṃ gatesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "For the sentient beings among whom these two things were widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.8"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ pañcavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ appekacce aḍḍhateyyavassasahassāyukā, appekacce dvevassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 5,000 years had some children who lived for 2,500 years, while others lived for 2,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "dn26:17.9"
msgid "Aḍḍhateyyavassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu abhijjhābyāpādā vepullamagamaṃsu. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 2,500 years, desire and ill will became widespread. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.10"
msgid "Abhijjhābyāpādesu vepullaṃ gatesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "For the sentient beings among whom desire and ill will were widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.11"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ aḍḍhateyyavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vassasahassāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 2,500 years had children who lived for 1,000 years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "dn26:17.12"
msgid "Vassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu micchādiṭṭhi vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for 1,000 years, wrong view became widespread. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.13"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhiyā vepullaṃ gatāya tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "For the sentient beings among whom wrong view was widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.14"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ vassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ pañcavassasatāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for 1,000 years had children who lived for five hundred years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn26:17.15"
msgid "Pañcavassasatāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu tayo dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu—"
msgstr "Among the people who lived for five hundred years, three things became widespread: "

msgctxt "dn26:17.16"
msgid "adhammarāgo visamalobho micchādhammo. "
msgstr "illicit desire, immoral greed, and wrong thoughts. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.17"
msgid "Tīsu dhammesu vepullaṃ gatesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "For the sentient beings among whom these three things were widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:17.18"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ pañcavassasatāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ appekacce aḍḍhateyyavassasatāyukā, appekacce dvevassasatāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for five hundred years had some children who lived for two hundred and fifty years, while others lived for two hundred years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "dn26:17.19"
msgid "Aḍḍhateyyavassasatāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ime dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu. "
msgstr "Among the people who lived for two hundred and fifty years, three things became widespread: "

msgctxt "dn26:17.20"
msgid "Amatteyyatā apetteyyatā asāmaññatā abrahmaññatā na kule jeṭṭhāpacāyitā. "
msgstr "lack of due respect for mother and father, ascetics and brahmins, and failure to honor the elders in the family. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs18, pts-vp-pli3.71, sc36
msgctxt "dn26:18.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, adhanānaṃ dhane ananuppadiyamāne dāliddiyaṃ vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, from not paying money to the penniless, all these things became widespread—poverty, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.2"
msgid "Dāliddiye vepullaṃ gate adinnādānaṃ vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "theft, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.3"
msgid "Adinnādāne vepullaṃ gate satthaṃ vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "swords, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.4"
msgid "Satthe vepullaṃ gate pāṇātipāto vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "killing, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.5"
msgid "Pāṇātipāte vepullaṃ gate musāvādo vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "lying, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.6"
msgid "Musāvāde vepullaṃ gate pisuṇā vācā vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "backbiting, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.7"
msgid "Pisuṇāya vācāya vepullaṃ gatāya kāmesumicchācāro vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "sexual misconduct, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.8"
msgid "Kāmesumicchācāre vepullaṃ gate dve dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu, pharusā vācā samphappalāpo ca. "
msgstr "harsh speech and talking nonsense, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.9"
msgid "Dvīsu dhammesu vepullaṃ gatesu abhijjhābyāpādā vepullamagamaṃsu. "
msgstr "desire and ill will, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.10"
msgid "Abhijjhābyāpādesu vepullaṃ gatesu micchādiṭṭhi vepullamagamāsi. "
msgstr "wrong view, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.11"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhiyā vepullaṃ gatāya tayo dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu, adhammarāgo visamalobho micchādhammo. "
msgstr "illicit desire, immoral greed, and wrong thoughts, "

msgctxt "dn26:18.12"
msgid "Tīsu dhammesu vepullaṃ gatesu ime dhammā vepullamagamaṃsu, amatteyyatā apetteyyatā asāmaññatā abrahmaññatā na kule jeṭṭhāpacāyitā. "
msgstr "and lack of due respect for mother and father, ascetics and brahmins, and failure to honor the elders in the family. "

msgctxt "dn26:18.13"
msgid "Imesu dhammesu vepullaṃ gatesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ āyupi parihāyi, vaṇṇopi parihāyi. "
msgstr "For the sentient beings among whom these things were widespread, their lifespan and beauty declined. "

msgctxt "dn26:18.14"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi parihāyamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi parihāyamānānaṃ aḍḍhateyyavassasatāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vassasatāyukā puttā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Those people who lived for two hundred and fifty years had children who lived for a hundred years. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:18.15"
msgid "5. Dasavassāyukasamaya "
msgstr "5. When People Live for Ten Years "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs19, sc37
msgctxt "dn26:19.1"
msgid "Bhavissati, bhikkhave, so samayo, yaṃ imesaṃ manussānaṃ dasavassāyukā puttā bhavissanti. "
msgstr "There will come a time, mendicants, when these people will have children who live for ten years. "

#. VAR: pañcavassikā → pañcamāsikā (si)
msgctxt "dn26:19.2"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu pañcavassikā kumārikā alaṃpateyyā bhavissanti. "
msgstr "Among the people who live for ten years, girls will be marriageable at five. "

msgctxt "dn26:19.3"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu imāni rasāni antaradhāyissanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The following flavors will disappear: "

msgctxt "dn26:19.4"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ loṇaṃ. "
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, molasses, and salt. "

# NOTE: Horner has “rye” for kudrūsaka, but rye is a European grain. Finger millet is a widespread secondary grain in India, which grows in places rice cannot. While in Sri Lanka I learned that it is grown in the South, where it is too hot and dry for rice. But with the influence of climate change, rice will soon be unviable and finger millet, or kurukkan, will become essential. When I learned of this I was immediately reminded of this passage. I have no idea whether the word kurukkan is related to kudrusaka, but some of the other Indic terms for this grain seem to be, eg. the Pahari term “kodra”, Garhwal “koda”.
#. VAR: aggaṃ bhojanānaṃ → aggabhojanaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:19.5"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu kudrūsako aggaṃ bhojanānaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "The best kind of food will be finger millet, "

msgctxt "dn26:19.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, etarahi sālimaṃsodano aggaṃ bhojanānaṃ; "
msgstr "just as fine rice with meat is the best kind of food today. "

msgctxt "dn26:19.7"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, dasavassāyukesu manussesu kudrūsako aggaṃ bhojanānaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: Comm has “Atibyādippissantīti ativiya dippissanti, ayameva vā pāṭho” so its mainline version must have been Atibyādippissanti or similar. But this leaves unexplained the long ā in the sandhi. At the same time, the sense of dippati is not entirely clear here. RD has “flourish”, MW has “prevail”, but neither of these is really what it means. If anything, its basic meaning of “appear, show” contrasts more directly with antaradhayati. However, note that ādippati occurs, I think, once elsewhere in the canon, in AN 7.66, which by coincidence or not, also concerns a myth of the future. There it refers to an erupting volcano. Given that this explains the long ā, and that the unusual and emphatic form suggests a powerful meaning, I suggest that the sense “explode” (in popularity, etc.) fits here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.72, sc38
msgctxt "dn26:19.8"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu dasa kusalakammapathā sabbena sabbaṃ antaradhāyissanti, dasa akusalakammapathā atibyādippissanti. "
msgstr "The ten ways of doing skillful deeds will totally disappear, and the ten ways of doing unskillful deeds will explode in popularity. "

msgctxt "dn26:19.9"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu kusalantipi na bhavissati, kuto pana kusalassa kārako. "
msgstr "Those people will not even have the word ‘skillful’, still less anyone who does what is skillful. "

msgctxt "dn26:19.10"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ye te bhavissanti amatteyyā apetteyyā asāmaññā abrahmaññā na kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino, te pujjā ca bhavissanti pāsaṃsā ca. "
msgstr "And anyone who disrespects mother and father, ascetics and brahmins, and fails to honor the elders in the family will be venerated and praised, "

msgctxt "dn26:19.11"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, etarahi matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino pujjā ca pāsaṃsā ca; "
msgstr "just as the opposite is venerated and praised today. "

msgctxt "dn26:19.12"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, dasavassāyukesu manussesu ye te bhavissanti amatteyyā apetteyyā asāmaññā abrahmaññā na kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino, te pujjā ca bhavissanti pāsaṃsā ca. "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: See AN 2.9.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs20, sc39
msgctxt "dn26:20.1"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu na bhavissati mātāti vā mātucchāti vā mātulānīti vā ācariyabhariyāti vā garūnaṃ dārāti vā. "
msgstr "There’ll be no recognition of the status of mother, aunts, or wives and partners of teachers and respected people. "

# NOTE: For sambheda, see AN 2.9=DN 26, AN 5.103 = AN 10.45, and DN 3. In each case the sense is not “breaking, destroying” as you might expect, but the dissolving of boundaries, resulting in promiscuity or leaking of secrets. Comm. to DN 26 has “Sambhedanti missībhāvaṃ, mariyādabhedaṃ vā.”
#. VAR: soṇasiṅgālā → soṇasigālā (bj, pts1) | soṇā sigālā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:20.2"
msgid "Sambhedaṃ loko gamissati yathā ajeḷakā kukkuṭasūkarā soṇasiṅgālā. "
msgstr "The world will become promiscuous, like goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and dogs and jackals. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.73, sc40
msgctxt "dn26:20.3"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ aññamaññamhi tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito bhavissati tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ. "
msgstr "They’ll be full of hostility towards each other, with acute ill will, malevolence, and thoughts of murder. "

msgctxt "dn26:20.4"
msgid "Mātupi puttamhi puttassapi mātari; "
msgstr "Even a mother will feel like this for her child, and the child for its mother, "

msgctxt "dn26:20.5"
msgid "pitupi puttamhi puttassapi pitari; "
msgstr "father for child, child for father, "

msgctxt "dn26:20.6"
msgid "bhātupi bhaginiyā bhaginiyāpi bhātari tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito bhavissati tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ. "
msgstr "brother for sister, and sister for brother. "

msgctxt "dn26:20.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, māgavikassa migaṃ disvā tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito hoti tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ; "
msgstr "They’ll be just like a deer hunter when he sees a deer—full of hostility, ill will, malevolence, and thoughts of killing. "

msgctxt "dn26:20.8"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, dasavassāyukesu manussesu tesaṃ sattānaṃ aññamaññamhi tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito bhavissati tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:20.9"
msgid "Mātupi puttamhi puttassapi mātari; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:20.10"
msgid "pitupi puttamhi puttassapi pitari; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn26:20.11"
msgid "bhātupi bhaginiyā bhaginiyāpi bhātari tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito bhavissati tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs21, sc41
msgctxt "dn26:21.1"
msgid "Dasavassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu sattāhaṃ satthantarakappo bhavissati. "
msgstr "Among the people who live for ten years, there will be an interregnum of swords lasting seven days. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.2"
msgid "Te aññamaññamhi migasaññaṃ paṭilabhissanti. "
msgstr "During that time they will see each other as beasts. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ tiṇhāni satthāni hatthesu pātubhavissanti. "
msgstr "Sharp swords will appear in their hands, "

#. VAR: voropessanti → voropissanti (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:21.4"
msgid "Te tiṇhena satthena ‘esa migo esa migo’ti aññamaññaṃ jīvitā voropessanti. "
msgstr "with which they’ll take each other’s life, crying, ‘It’s a beast! It’s a beast!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "dn26:21.5"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ ekaccānaṃ evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "But then some of those beings will think, "

#. VAR: tiṇagahanaṃ → … gahaṇaṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: kañci → kiñci (mr)
msgctxt "dn26:21.6"
msgid "‘mā ca mayaṃ kañci, mā ca amhe koci, yannūna mayaṃ tiṇagahanaṃ vā vanagahanaṃ vā rukkhagahanaṃ vā nadīviduggaṃ vā pabbatavisamaṃ vā pavisitvā vanamūlaphalāhārā yāpeyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Let us neither be perpetrators nor victims! Why don’t we hide in thick grass, thick jungle, thick trees, inaccessible riverlands, or rugged mountains and survive on forest roots and fruits?’ "

msgctxt "dn26:21.7"
msgid "Te tiṇagahanaṃ vā vanagahanaṃ vā rukkhagahanaṃ vā nadīviduggaṃ vā pabbatavisamaṃ vā pavisitvā sattāhaṃ vanamūlaphalāhārā yāpessanti. "
msgstr "So that’s what they do. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: According to Cone (gāyati), sabhāgāyissanti is correct and PTS sabhā gāyissanti incorrect. Sabhāgāyissanti = sabhāga + āyissanti = will come together. samassāsissanti = sama + sāsati is absent from some manuscripts and is not commented on; I think it’s dubious.
msgctxt "dn26:21.8"
msgid "Te tassa sattāhassa accayena tiṇagahanā vanagahanā rukkhagahanā nadīviduggā pabbatavisamā nikkhamitvā aññamaññaṃ āliṅgitvā sabhāgāyissanti samassāsissanti: "
msgstr "When those seven days have passed, having emerged from their hiding places and embraced each other, they will come together in one voice and cry, "

# NOTE: Diṭṭhā here probably doesn’t mean “seen, but” hurrah!"The plural for satt-a is puzzling; one var in PTS edition has the second as satta = voc sing, which I take as correct. Otherwise we would expect bhonto sattā, but this disagrees with the verb.
msgctxt "dn26:21.9"
msgid "‘diṭṭhā, bho, sattā jīvasi, diṭṭhā, bho, sattā jīvasī’ti. "
msgstr "‘How fantastic, dear being, you live! How fantastic, dear being, you live!’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:21.10"
msgid "6. Āyuvaṇṇādivaḍḍhanakathā "
msgstr "6. The Period of Growth "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.74, sc43
msgctxt "dn26:21.11"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "Then those beings will think, "

msgctxt "dn26:21.12"
msgid "‘mayaṃ kho akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samādānahetu evarūpaṃ āyataṃ ñātikkhayaṃ pattā. "
msgstr "‘It’s because we undertook unskillful things that we suffered such an extensive loss of our relatives. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.13"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ kusalaṃ kareyyāma. "
msgstr "We’d better do what’s skillful. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.14"
msgid "Kiṃ kusalaṃ kareyyāma? "
msgstr "What skillful thing should we do? "

msgctxt "dn26:21.15"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ pāṇātipātā virameyyāma, idaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ samādāya vatteyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we refrain from killing living creatures? Having undertaken this skillful thing we’ll live by it.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:21.16"
msgid "Te pāṇātipātā viramissanti, idaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ samādāya vattissanti. "
msgstr "So that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.17"
msgid "Te kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samādānahetu āyunāpi vaḍḍhissanti, vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhissanti. "
msgstr "Because of undertaking this skillful thing, their lifespan and beauty will grow. "

msgctxt "dn26:21.18"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi vaḍḍhamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhamānānaṃ dasavassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vīsativassāyukā puttā bhavissanti. "
msgstr "Those people who live for ten years will have children who live for twenty years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs22, sc44
msgctxt "dn26:22.1"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ, bhikkhave, sattānaṃ evaṃ bhavissati: "
msgstr "Then those beings will think, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.2"
msgid "‘mayaṃ kho kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samādānahetu āyunāpi vaḍḍhāma, vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhāma. "
msgstr "‘Because of undertaking this skillful thing, our lifespan and beauty are growing. "

msgctxt "dn26:22.3"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ bhiyyoso mattāya kusalaṃ kareyyāma. "
msgstr "Why don’t we do even more skillful things? "

msgctxt "dn26:22.4"
msgid "Kiṃ kusalaṃ kareyyāma? "
msgstr "What skillful thing should we do? "

msgctxt "dn26:22.5"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ adinnādānā virameyyāma … "
msgstr "Why don’t we refrain from stealing … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.6"
msgid "kāmesumicchācārā virameyyāma … "
msgstr "sexual misconduct … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.7"
msgid "musāvādā virameyyāma … "
msgstr "lying … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.8"
msgid "pisuṇāya vācāya virameyyāma … "
msgstr "backbiting … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.9"
msgid "pharusāya vācāya virameyyāma … "
msgstr "harsh speech … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.10"
msgid "samphappalāpā virameyyāma … "
msgstr "and talking nonsense. "

msgctxt "dn26:22.11"
msgid "abhijjhaṃ pajaheyyāma … "
msgstr "Why don’t we give up covetousness … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.12"
msgid "byāpādaṃ pajaheyyāma … "
msgstr "ill will … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.13"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhiṃ pajaheyyāma … "
msgstr "wrong view … "

msgctxt "dn26:22.14"
msgid "tayo dhamme pajaheyyāma—"
msgstr "three things: "

msgctxt "dn26:22.15"
msgid "adhammarāgaṃ visamalobhaṃ micchādhammaṃ … "
msgstr "illicit desire, immoral greed, and wrong thoughts. "

msgctxt "dn26:22.16"
msgid "yannūna mayaṃ matteyyā assāma petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino, idaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ samādāya vatteyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we pay due respect to mother and father, ascetics and brahmins, honoring the elders in our families? Having undertaken this skillful thing we’ll live by it.’ "

msgctxt "dn26:22.17"
msgid "Te matteyyā bhavissanti petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino, idaṃ kusalaṃ dhammaṃ samādāya vattissanti. "
msgstr "So that’s what they do. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.75, sc45
msgctxt "dn26:22.18"
msgid "Te kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samādānahetu āyunāpi vaḍḍhissanti, vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhissanti. "
msgstr "Because of undertaking this skillful thing, their lifespan and beauty will grow. "

msgctxt "dn26:22.19"
msgid "Tesaṃ āyunāpi vaḍḍhamānānaṃ vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhamānānaṃ vīsativassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ cattārīsavassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "Those people who live for twenty years will have children who live for forty years. "

msgctxt "dn26:22.20"
msgid "cattārīsavassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ asītivassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "Those people who live for forty years will have children who live for eighty years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.21"
msgid "asītivassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ saṭṭhivassasatāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "then a hundred and sixty years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.22"
msgid "saṭṭhivassasatāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vīsatitivassasatāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "three hundred and twenty years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.23"
msgid "vīsatitivassasatāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ cattārīsachabbassasatāyukā puttā bhavissanti. "
msgstr "six hundred and forty years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.24"
msgid "Cattārīsachabbassasatāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ dvevassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "2,000 years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.25"
msgid "dvevassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ cattārivassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "4,000 years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.26"
msgid "cattārivassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ aṭṭhavassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "8,000 years, "

msgctxt "dn26:22.27"
msgid "aṭṭhavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ vīsativassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "20,000 years, "

#. REF: pts-cs23
msgctxt "dn26:23.1"
msgid "vīsativassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ cattārīsavassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "40,000 years, "

msgctxt "dn26:23.2"
msgid "cattārīsavassasahassāyukānaṃ manussānaṃ asītivassasahassāyukā puttā bhavissanti … "
msgstr "and finally 80,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn26:23.3"
msgid "asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu pañcavassasatikā kumārikā alaṃpateyyā bhavissanti. "
msgstr "Among the people who live for 80,000 years, girls will be marriageable at five hundred. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:23.4"
msgid "7. Saṅkharājauppatti "
msgstr "7. The Time of King Saṅkha "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "dn26:23.5"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu tayo ābādhā bhavissanti, icchā, anasanaṃ, jarā. "
msgstr "Among the people who live for 80,000 years, there will be just three afflictions: greed, starvation, and old age. "

msgctxt "dn26:23.6"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ayaṃ jambudīpo iddho ceva bhavissati phīto ca, kukkuṭasampātikā gāmanigamarājadhāniyo. "
msgstr "India will be successful and prosperous. The villages, towns, and capital cities will be no more than a chicken’s flight apart. "

#. VAR: saravanaṃ → sāravanaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn26:23.7"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ayaṃ jambudīpo avīci maññe phuṭo bhavissati manussehi, seyyathāpi naḷavanaṃ vā saravanaṃ vā. "
msgstr "And the land will be as crowded as hell, just full of people, like a thicket of rushes or reeds. "

msgctxt "dn26:23.8"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ayaṃ bārāṇasī ketumatī nāma rājadhānī bhavissati iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ca ākiṇṇamanussā ca subhikkhā ca. "
msgstr "The royal capital will be our Benares, but renamed Ketumati. And it will be successful, prosperous, populous, full of people, with plenty of food. "

msgctxt "dn26:23.9"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu imasmiṃ jambudīpe caturāsītinagarasahassāni bhavissanti ketumatīrājadhānīpamukhāni. "
msgstr "There will be 84,000 cities in India, with the royal capital of Ketumati foremost. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs24
msgctxt "dn26:24.1"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu ketumatiyā rājadhāniyā saṅkho nāma rājā uppajjissati cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr "And in the royal capital of Ketumati a king named Saṅkha will arise, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion will extend to all four sides, he will achieve stability in the country, and possess the seven treasures. "

msgctxt "dn26:24.2"
msgid "Tassimāni satta ratanāni bhavissanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "He will have the following seven treasures: "

msgctxt "dn26:24.3"
msgid "cakkaratanaṃ hatthiratanaṃ assaratanaṃ maṇiratanaṃ itthiratanaṃ gahapatiratanaṃ pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr "the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure. "

msgctxt "dn26:24.4"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavissanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr "He will have over a thousand sons who are valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of his enemies. "

msgctxt "dn26:24.5"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasissati. "
msgstr "After conquering this land girt by sea, he will reign by principle, without rod or sword. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:24.6"
msgid "8. Metteyyabuddhuppāda "
msgstr "8. The Arising of the Buddha Metteyya "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs25, pts-vp-pli3.76, sc47
msgctxt "dn26:25.1"
msgid "Asītivassasahassāyukesu, bhikkhave, manussesu metteyyo nāma bhagavā loke uppajjissati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā. "
msgstr "And the Blessed One named Metteyya will arise in the world—perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed—"

msgctxt "dn26:25.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpāhametarahi loke uppanno arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā. "
msgstr "just as I have arisen today. "

msgctxt "dn26:25.3"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedessati, seyyathāpāhametarahi imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedemi. "
msgstr "He will realize with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and make it known to others, just as I do today. "

msgctxt "dn26:25.4"
msgid "So dhammaṃ desessati ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsessati; "
msgstr "He will teach the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he will reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure, "

msgctxt "dn26:25.5"
msgid "seyyathāpāhametarahi dhammaṃ desemi ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsemi. "
msgstr "just as I do today. "

# NOTE: Interesting choice of verb here: pariharati is not lead or command, but nurture, like a mother the child in her womb.
#. VAR: anekasahassaṃ → aneka­sata­sahas­saṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn26:25.6"
msgid "So anekasahassaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ pariharissati, seyyathāpāhametarahi anekasataṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ pariharāmi. "
msgstr "He will look after a Saṅgha of many thousand mendicants, just as I look after a Saṅgha of many hundreds today. "

# NOTE: This oddity is found in Bhaddaji’s verses at Thag 2.22 and the full story at Ja 264. While the Comm. stories, followed by RD and MW, say this is a palace, the verses there clearly depict a sacrificial post, yūpa. Probably the original meaning of this reference was lost early on, and the story filled in.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs26, pts-vp-pli3.77, sc48
msgctxt "dn26:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, saṅkho nāma rājā yo so yūpo raññā mahāpanādena kārāpito. "
msgstr "Then King Saṅkha will have the sacrificial post that had been built by King Mahāpanāda raised up. "

msgctxt "dn26:26.2"
msgid "Taṃ yūpaṃ ussāpetvā ajjhāvasitvā taṃ datvā vissajjitvā samaṇabrāhmaṇakapaṇaddhikavaṇibbakayācakānaṃ dānaṃ datvā metteyyassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissati. "
msgstr "After staying there, he will give it away to ascetics and brahmins, paupers, vagrants, travelers, and beggars. Then, having shaved off his hair and beard and dressed in ocher robes, he will go forth from the lay life to homelessness in the Buddha Metteyya’s presence. "

msgctxt "dn26:26.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissati. "
msgstr "Soon after going forth, living withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, he will realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He will live having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs27, sc49
msgctxt "dn26:27.1"
msgid "Attadīpā, bhikkhave, viharatha attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā. "
msgstr "Mendicants, be your own island, your own refuge, with no other refuge. Let the teaching be your island and your refuge, with no other refuge. "

msgctxt "dn26:27.2"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant do this? "

msgctxt "dn26:27.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "dn26:27.4"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "dn26:27.5"
msgid "citte cittānupassī … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "dn26:27.6"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "dn26:27.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is their own island, their own refuge, with no other refuge. That’s how they let the teaching be their island and their refuge, with no other refuge. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn26:27.8"
msgid "9. Bhikkhunoāyuvaṇṇādivaḍḍhanakathā "
msgstr "9. On Long Life and Beauty for Mendicants "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs28, sc50
msgctxt "dn26:28.1"
msgid "Gocare, bhikkhave, caratha sake pettike visaye. "
msgstr "Mendicants, you should roam inside your own territory, the domain of your fathers. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.2"
msgid "Gocare, bhikkhave, carantā sake pettike visaye āyunāpi vaḍḍhissatha, vaṇṇenapi vaḍḍhissatha, sukhenapi vaḍḍhissatha, bhogenapi vaḍḍhissatha, balenapi vaḍḍhissatha. "
msgstr "Doing so, you will grow in life span, beauty, happiness, wealth, and power. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn26:28.3"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno āyusmiṃ? "
msgstr "And what is long life for a mendicant? "

msgctxt "dn26:28.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.5"
msgid "vīriyasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.6"
msgid "cittasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.7"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.8"
msgid "So imesaṃ catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā. "
msgstr "Having developed and cultivated these four bases of psychic power they may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.9"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno āyusmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is long life for a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.78, sc52
msgctxt "dn26:28.10"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno vaṇṇasmiṃ? "
msgstr "And what is beauty for a mendicant? "

msgctxt "dn26:28.11"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno, aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.12"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno vaṇṇasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is beauty for a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "dn26:28.13"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sukhasmiṃ? "
msgstr "And what is happiness for a mendicant? "

msgctxt "dn26:28.14"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.15"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "dn26:28.16"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "dn26:28.17"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.18"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno, sukhasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is happiness for a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "dn26:28.19"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhogasmiṃ? "
msgstr "And what is wealth for a mendicant? "

msgctxt "dn26:28.20"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati tathā dutiyaṃ. Tathā tatiyaṃ. Tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a monk meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.21"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion … "

msgctxt "dn26:28.22"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "rejoicing … "

msgctxt "dn26:28.23"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati. Tathā dutiyaṃ. Tathā tatiyaṃ. Tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.24"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhogasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is wealth for a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc55
msgctxt "dn26:28.25"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno balasmiṃ? "
msgstr "And what is power for a mendicant? "

msgctxt "dn26:28.26"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.27"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno balasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is power for a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.79, sc56
msgctxt "dn26:28.28"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekabalampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ duppasahaṃ, yathayidaṃ, bhikkhave, mārabalaṃ. "
msgstr "Mendicants, I do not see a single power so hard to defeat as the power of Māra. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.29"
msgid "Kusalānaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ samādānahetu evamidaṃ puññaṃ pavaḍḍhatī”ti. "
msgstr "It is due to undertaking skillful qualities that this merit grows.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc57
msgctxt "dn26:28.30"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn26:28.31"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn26:28.32"
msgid "Cakkavattisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

